    "refcode_short": "CSW 100.2",
    "refcode_long": "Counsels on Sabbath School Work, p. 100.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Remember that you cannot read hearts. You do not know the motives which prompted the actions that to you look wrong. There are many who have not received a right education; their characters are warped, they are hard and gnarled, and seem to be crooked in every way. But the grace of Christ can transform them. Never cast them aside, never drive them to discouragement or despair by saying, &ldquo;You have disappointed me, and I will not try to help you.&rdquo; A few words spoken hastily under provocation,&mdash;just what we <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"101\"></span> think they deserve,&mdash;may cut the cords of influence that should have bound their hearts to ours.",
    "puborder": 282,
    "translations": [
