    "refcode_long": "Counsels on Sabbath School Work, p. 101.3 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Until the judgment you will never know the influence of a kind, considerate course toward the inconsistent, the unreasonable, the unworthy. When we meet with ingratitude and betrayal of sacred trusts, we are roused to show our contempt or indignation. This the guilty expect, they are prepared for it. But kind forbearance takes them by surprise, and often awakens their better impulses, and arouses a longing for a nobler life.&mdash;<span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"TSS 117.1\" data-link=\"121.484\"><em>Testimonies on Sabbath-School Work</em>, 117</span>.",
